=Create an HTML page that beautifully presents the following answer: {{ $json.output }}. Follow these guidelines:
Structure: 
Use semantic HTML5 (e.g., <header>, <main>, <footer>).
Include a clean, modern design with a responsive layout.
Add a title and meta tags for proper rendering.
Styling:
Use CSS (inline or in a <style> tag) for styling.
Apply a professional color scheme (e.g., soft blues, whites, or neutral tones).
Ensure fonts are clean and readable (e.g., Roboto, Open Sans, or similar via Google Fonts).
Make the layout responsive for mobile and desktop.
Tables (if present in the answer):
Style tables with:
Borders, padding, and hover effects for rows.
Alternating row colors for readability.
A bold header row with a distinct background color.
Center-align numerical data and left-align text data.
Example CSS: 
css
table {
    border-collapse: collapse;
    width: 100%;
    margin: 20px 0;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
}
th, td {
    padding: 12px;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    text-align: left;
}
th {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: white;
}
tr:nth-child(even) {
    background-color: #f2f2f2;
}
tr:hover {
    background-color: #e0e0e0;
}
Graphs (if present in the answer):
Use a JavaScript library like Chart.js to render graphs.
Include the Chart.js CDN in the HTML.
Convert any graph data in the answer into a visually appealing chart (e.g., bar, line, or pie chart, depending on the data).
Style charts with:
Smooth animations.
A color palette that matches the page theme.
Clear labels and legends.
Ensure graphs are responsive and fit well on all screen sizes.
General Content:
Format text with proper headings (<h1>, <h2>, etc.), paragraphs, and lists.
Highlight key points with subtle background colors or borders.
Add subtle animations (e.g., fade-in for content) using CSS.
Output:
Provide the complete HTML code, including all CSS and JavaScript.
Ensure the code is ready to be saved as a .html file and opened in a browser.
Test that tables and graphs (if any) render correctly and look beautiful.
You can replace "[Insert Answer Here]" with the specific answer you want to convert into HTML. If you provide me with an answer, I can generate the HTML code directly for you!
